is ready for pickup.

18:05.961 --> 18:08.087
- This is
your local Rite Aid Pharmacy.

18:08.088 --> 18:10.173
Your prescription
will be available

18:10.174 --> 18:12.717
for three more days.

18:16.388 --> 18:18.472
- This is
your local Rite Aid Pharmacy.

18:18.473 --> 18:20.766
Your prescription
has been canceled.

18:20.767 --> 18:22.852
Please call
your doctor's office.

18:22.853 --> 18:24.520
- I think that's better
than a coffee.

18:25.856 --> 18:27.858
You're welcome.

18:30.569 --> 18:32.320
- Did you cum?

18:32.321 --> 18:33.905
- Um, no, I don't think...

18:33.906 --> 18:36.116
uh, I don't think
it's gonna happen today.

18:47.586 --> 18:48.837
- Are you okay?

18:48.838 --> 18:50.505
- Yeah, I think it's just
a possible side effect

18:50.506 --> 18:52.465
of the medication
I'm taking.

18:52.466 --> 18:54.759
- You do...

18:54.760 --> 18:58.804
seem like you're...
a little better, I think.

18:58.805 --> 19:01.474
- Well, I read somewhere
that sometimes,

19:01.475 --> 19:05.437
your body feels it
before your head does.

19:14.071 --> 19:16.155
- I wish I had
a better understanding

19:16.156 --> 19:18.699
of what you're going through.
- Oh, it's hard to describe.

19:18.700 --> 19:21.035
- You're an English teacher.

19:21.036 --> 19:23.664
Give me a metaphor.
- I don't know!

19:26.375 --> 19:28.960
- I read an article

19:28.961 --> 19:31.546
that said it's like a...

19:31.547 --> 19:35.508
like a fog
descending over everything.

19:37.302 --> 19:39.428
- Like that?

19:39.429 --> 19:41.431
- Kind of.

19:43.725 --> 19:45.226
- Please just tell me

19:45.227 --> 19:48.437
if there's anything

19:48.438 --> 19:50.064
I can do to help.

19:50.065 --> 19:51.566
- Oh, yeah.

19:51.567 --> 19:53.318
- Anything.

19:56.029 --> 19:58.239
Even if it's giving you space,

19:58.240 --> 20:01.242
which, you know,
is the hardest thing

20:01.243 --> 20:04.829
you could ask me to do.

20:04.830 --> 20:08.291
But I love you that much.

20:08.292 --> 20:11.377
- That is what I need.

20:15.841 --> 20:17.675
- Then...

20:17.676 --> 20:21.679
I can start by
taking a shower,

20:21.680 --> 20:24.265
and that will buy you
ten minutes.

20:24.266 --> 20:27.059
Mm, twenty-five.

20:51.877 --> 20:53.336
- Hey, it's, uh...
it's Danny.

20:53.337 --> 20:55.505
I, uh...

20:55.506 --> 20:57.340
I do... I don't know why

20:57.341 --> 20:59.342
I even called you.
I...

20:59.343 --> 21:02.303
You're never even gonna get
this message.

21:02.304 --> 21:04.430
Yeah.

21:04.431 --> 21:06.807
I guess I just wanted
to hear your voice.

21:09.520 --> 21:11.604
This is weird.

21:11.605 --> 21:12.856
Sorry.

21:15.025 --> 21:18.027
Um...

21:18.028 --> 21:21.280
I was procrastinating
the other day

21:21.281 --> 21:23.407
and I was flipping
through my phone,

21:23.408 --> 21:27.828
and I found this old
credit card bill

21:27.829 --> 21:30.540
I hadn't paid.

21:30.541 --> 21:34.418
Um, I donated to this thing.

21:34.419 --> 21:39.715
The last male
northern white rhino was sick.

21:39.716 --> 21:41.843
And I hid the emails

21:41.844 --> 21:43.511
because I didn't want Leigh
to find out about it,

21:43.512 --> 21:46.889
and I guess I forgot to pay it.

21:46.890 --> 21:50.977
W... anyway, um...

21:50.978 --> 21:52.478
I hadn't heard
about the rhino,

21:52.479 --> 21:57.108
so I looked him up,

21:57.109 --> 22:01.404
and it turns out he died.

22:01.405 --> 22:03.448
Months ago, actually.

22:06.702 --> 22:10.246
Um...

22:10.247 --> 22:14.584
The whole world just
didn't care about him.

22:14.585 --> 22:17.003
We killed off
every single creature like him,

22:17.004 --> 22:20.923
and now he's gone.

22:20.924 --> 22:22.800
- Why don't you want Leigh
to know?

22:22.801 --> 22:24.427
- Uh, because I always donate

22:24.428 --> 22:25.803
to bummer things like that,

22:25.804 --> 22:27.972
and I shouldn't
be spending the money,

22:27.973 --> 22:30.600
and e... I'll... I'll just put
the credit card

22:30.601 --> 22:33.102
in the freezer.
- Why can't you...

22:33.103 --> 22:34.854
just tell Leigh about it?

22:34.855 --> 22:38.482
- She doesn't know
what it's really like.

22:38.483 --> 22:40.151
She thinks it's like a fog,

22:40.152 --> 22:41.278
because someone
described it like that

22:41.278 --> 22:42.154
in an article or something,

22:42.155 --> 22:45.281
but that's... that's not
how it feels to me.

22:45.282 --> 22:46.949
- What does it feel like
for you?

22:46.950 --> 22:48.826
- The opposite.

22:48.827 --> 22:51.329
It feels like a bracing wind

22:51.330 --> 22:53.289
that blows...
blows the fog away

22:53.290 --> 22:55.416
and reveals the whole truth

22:55.417 --> 23:00.087
of the world underneath,
and it's...

23:00.088 --> 23:04.008
Everyone else is in the fog.
They can't see it, but I can,

23:04.009 --> 23:07.261
and it's all ugly
and hopeless.

23:07.262 --> 23:08.930
- Is that
the depression talking?

23:08.931 --> 23:11.516
- No, no, it's me talking.

23:11.517 --> 23:13.017
- The disease

23:13.018 --> 23:14.685
makes you see the world
that way.

23:14.686 --> 23:16.479
- No, the disease
isn't dangerous

23:16.480 --> 23:17.813
because it tells me lies.

23:17.814 --> 23:22.276
The disease is dangerous
because it tells me the truth.

23:22.277 --> 23:24.530
- Matt...

23:28.659 --> 23:31.410
You have to open yourself up

23:31.411 --> 23:33.204
to the possibility

23:33.205 --> 23:35.332
that you can be happy.

23:43.423 --> 23:45.007
- I was thinking
about this time

23:45.008 --> 23:46.467
we were driving to Vegas.

23:46.468 --> 23:48.803
I was sleeping, and...

23:48.804 --> 23:52.056
you woke me up
because there was actually

23:52.057 --> 23:53.641
a tumbleweed blowing by,

23:53.642 --> 23:56.644
and you knew
it would make me laugh.

23:58.522 --> 24:00.356
And I did.

24:00.357 --> 24:02.149
I laughed so hard.
It...

24:02.150 --> 24:03.694
- Matt Greer?

24:05.153 --> 24:07.989
- Not saying
I don't... laugh anymore,

24:07.990 --> 24:11.200
but... not like you
made me laugh.

24:11.201 --> 24:12.535
- Sorry I'm late, but I swear,

24:12.536 --> 24:15.121
being an editor's like being
a firefighter on the Sun,

24:15.122 --> 24:16.497
which is why it's so nice

24:16.498 --> 24:17.999
when I get
to make someone's day.

24:18.000 --> 24:19.251
Here's the deal:

24:19.252 --> 24:20.877
You're a better writer
than artist,

24:20.878 --> 24:22.171
and there's a few key panels

24:22.172 --> 24:23.588
I want you to take
another crack at,

24:23.589 --> 24:26.048
and obviously, you gotta finish
that last chapter,

24:26.049 --> 24:28.843
but I know you can get there.
- Uh, sure.

24:28.844 --> 24:32.388
- Sorry. I'm totally
burying the lede here.

24:32.389 --> 24:34.724
We're gonna publish you.

24:36.435 --> 24:38.561
- We just gotta nail those
last few pages and I'm...

24:45.319 --> 24:47.737
Congratulations, Matt.

24:47.738 --> 24:49.530
Welcome to the club.

25:04.046 --> 25:06.047
Matt, dude.
Joe Tsang.

25:06.048 --> 25:07.257
It's been three weeks.
Where'd you go?

25:07.258 --> 25:09.550
I've been emailing you.
Hit me back.

25:17.267 --> 25:20.144
- Hey.
- Hey.

25:20.145 --> 25:21.979
- What's going on?

25:21.980 --> 25:24.315
- It's Jules.
Her car

25:24.316 --> 25:26.609
quote-unquote broke down
in Victorville,

25:26.610 --> 25:30.154
so I'm not... I'm not
gonna make it for dinner.

25:30.155 --> 25:31.948
- Uh, then don't give it
a second thought.

25:31.949 --> 25:33.699
Just go do
what you've gotta do.

25:33.700 --> 25:35.535
- You're the greatest.
I'm so sorry.

25:35.536 --> 25:36.828
I'll make it up to you
tomorrow.

25:36.829 --> 25:39.205
- No, don't... don't... I...

25:39.206 --> 25:41.082
Yeah, you better.

25:43.043 --> 25:44.877
Hey, I'll see you later, okay?

25:44.878 --> 25:48.047
- Okay, I love you.
- Yeah, love you too.

25:48.048 --> 25:49.382
Bye.

25:58.308 --> 25:59.725
- I went
for a hike today.

25:59.726 --> 26:02.103
What do you think of that?

26:02.104 --> 26:05.231
I'm at the spot where, um...

26:05.232 --> 26:07.358
Anyway, I'm looking
straight down

26:07.359 --> 26:10.278
the side of this cliff, man.
It's no joke.

26:10.279 --> 26:13.906
But I guess
you already knew that.

26:13.907 --> 26:16.325
Was it muddy up there?

26:16.326 --> 26:17.827
You never replaced
those raggedy-ass boots,

26:17.828 --> 26:19.370
did you?

26:21.790 --> 26:24.125
I'm just trying
to understand...

26:24.126 --> 26:25.252
what happened,
since you can't

26:25.253 --> 26:27.837
explain it to me.

26:27.838 --> 26:29.672
Those last few seconds

26:29.673 --> 26:32.550
on the way down,

26:32.551 --> 26:34.385
what was going
through your head?

26:41.393 --> 26:43.561
Where are you going?

26:43.562 --> 26:44.979
- I'm gonna go
for a hike.

26:44.980 --> 26:46.647
- I'm gonna come with you.

26:47.942 --> 26:50.359
Just give me ten minutes
to get ready.

26:52.154 --> 26:54.030
And three more hours
to sleep.

26:54.031 --> 26:56.032
- You were up all night.
It's okay.

26:56.033 --> 26:57.617
- Mm, okay.

26:57.618 --> 26:58.911
I love you.

26:58.911 --> 27:00.204
- I love you too.

27:17.679 --> 27:20.389
- You've done
that hike a hundred times,

27:20.390 --> 27:24.185
and I've done it with you
at least 20.

27:30.150 --> 27:31.651
I want to believe
this was an accident,

27:31.652 --> 27:33.194
but I'm standing here,
looking down,

27:33.195 --> 27:36.697
and... I just don't know.

28:13.443 --> 28:15.486
- I think I want a party.
- You do?

28:15.487 --> 28:16.904
- I do.
- A party?

28:16.905 --> 28:18.990
- Mm-hmm. Like a big party.

28:18.991 --> 28:20.992
- Okay.

28:20.993 --> 28:22.202
- Leigh, I've been trying
to give you

28:22.202 --> 28:23.370
your column back for months.

28:23.371 --> 28:27.248
- I-I know you waited on me,
and the good news is,

28:27.249 --> 28:29.083
is that I'm done
putting my life on hold

28:29.084 --> 28:30.127
and I'm ready to do this.

28:30.127 --> 28:31.170
- Are you okay?

28:31.171 --> 28:35.423
You've invited 657 people
to my house tonight.

28:35.424 --> 28:37.300
- Well, it's a last-minute
invite on a Tuesday.

28:37.301 --> 28:39.510
If 30 people show up, it's
gonna be a Christmas miracle.

28:39.511 --> 28:43.431
